Creating Visualizations 14

- Download the Tornado 2.0.1 Chart by (1) Click to import a custom visual ---> (2) choose import from marketplace

- (3) Find Tornado ---> (4) Click Add


Choose the Tornado Chart from Visualizations  ---> Drag and drop the SortDate column to Group  ---> Drag and drop the OpenRate and BounceRate to Values.


Change the visualization of the Tornado Chart

- (1) Click to the Tornado Chart

- (2) Click to Format

- (3) Click to Title ---> Turn On

- (4) Change Title to OpenRate and BounceRate

- (5) Change the Font color to White and the Background color to Green

- (6) Choose the middle Alignment

- (7) Change the Text size to 11


- (1) In Axis change the BounceRate to 0.01 ---> (2) Turn Data Labels to On ---> (3) Change the Decimal Places to 2.

- In Data color change the OpenRate to Green and BounceRate to Yellow.


OpenRate Month over Month - This measure help us to show the fluctuation of the Open Rate Month over Month.

Create MoM% Measure

Dax MoM% = IF(ISFILTERED('MailChimp'[SortDate]),

                        ERROR("Time intelligence quick measures can only be grouped or filtered by the Power BI-               provided date hierarchy or primary date column."),

       VAR __PREV_MONTH =CALCULATE( [OpenRate], DATEADD('MailChimp'[SortDate].[Date], 1,MONTH))

       RETURN DIVIDE([OpenRate] - __PREV_MONTH, __PREV_MONTH))


- (1) Choose Clustered column chart from visualizations

- (2) Drag and drop the SoftDate column to Axis ---> delete Year, Quarter, and Day

- (3) Drag and drop MoM% measure to values


Change the visualization of the OpenRate Month over Month visualization

- (1) Turn Data labels to On

- (2) Turn Title to On

- (3) Change Title to OpenRate MoM

- (4) Change the Font color to White and the Background color to Green

- (5) Choose the middle Alignment

- (6) Change the Text size to 11
